It's Nam Yoon-seo.

7
00:01:01,519 --> 00:01:03,104
Is that your name, ma'am?

8
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:06,483
No. My name is Kim Hye-joo.

9
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:08,568
Nam Yoon-seo is my daughter's name.

10
00:01:08,651 --> 00:01:09,736
When was she born?

11
00:01:09,819 --> 00:01:11,696
In 2008. She's in 8th grade.

12
00:01:11,780 --> 00:01:13,406
She attends Jicheong Middle School.

13
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:14,657
What's your home address?

14
00:01:14,741 --> 00:01:16,618
It's 14, Sumyeong-ro 3-gil, Sinyang-gu.

15
00:01:17,118 --> 00:01:18,328
What's your phone number?

16
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:22,040
Look. I think my daughter
ran away from home.

17
00:01:22,123 --> 00:01:23,458
As in it was voluntary?

18
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:25,960
You don't think she's been abducted
or gone missing?

19
00:01:26,044 --> 00:01:26,920
Abducted?

20
00:01:27,712 --> 00:01:30,423
It's uncommon,

21
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:32,675
but it's also a possibility.

22
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:36,971
It shouldn't be ruled out,
particularly with women or teenagers.

23
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:41,726
Why do you think she ran away from home?

24
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:44,604
Did she text or leave you a note?

25
00:01:44,687 --> 00:01:46,397
No, she didn't.

26
00:01:47,398 --> 00:01:49,484
But we had an argument earlier today.

27
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:53,238
You had an argument. I see.

28
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:57,450
Has she ever run away from home before?

29
00:01:57,534 --> 00:02:00,203
No, she's not the type to do such a thing.

30
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:06,668
This is

31
