to any of his campaignsâ€¦

260
00:15:15,372 --> 00:15:20,377
No, she's never shown herself
in public at all.

261
00:15:20,461 --> 00:15:23,672
The other wives do their best
to win over the electorate.

262
00:15:24,256 --> 00:15:26,050
This is what everyone's been thinking

263
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:28,052
during the last general election.

264
00:15:28,886 --> 00:15:30,596
According to Mr. Jang,

265
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:34,141
she had allowed her husband
to run for office under that condition.

266
00:15:34,224 --> 00:15:38,312
She apparently didn't want
any part in his political career.

267
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:43,150
In a way, Assemblyman Nam isâ€¦
How should I put this?

268
00:15:43,901 --> 00:15:45,110
What's to think about?

269
00:15:45,194 --> 00:15:46,570
He's the perfect husband.

270
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:49,531
Not many husbands would
ever go that far to protect their wives

271
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:52,826
regardless of what people say
behind their backs.

272
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:55,663
Did you have a big fight yesterday?

273
00:15:55,746 --> 00:15:56,997
No.

274
00:15:57,081 --> 00:16:00,501
You got pretty riled up talking about
other husbands just now.

275
00:16:00,584 --> 00:16:02,002
Are you okay?

276
00:16:02,086 --> 00:16:03,045
About tonight's dinnerâ€¦

277
00:16:03,128 --> 00:16:04,922
Ms. Woo wants to see you.

278
00:16:05,005 --> 00:16:06,048
Okay.

279
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:13,931
Hello, Assemblyman Kang.

280
00:16:16,183 --> 00:16:17,559
Who was he again?

281
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:20,688
Are you a secretary?

282
00:16:21,897 --> 00:16:24,274
It's Assemblyman Nam Joong-do
of the Daehan Party.

283
00:16:24,358 --> 00:16:27,277
I see. You're an assemblyman.

284
00:16:27,361 --> 00:16:28,195
Goodness.

285
00:16:29,029 --> 00:16:30,406
My apologies.

286
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:32,950
You just looked so young

287
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:35,911
that I thought you were
an assemblyman's secretary.

288
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:38,831
That's okay.

289
00:16:39,331 --> 00:16:40,958
When you were my age,

290
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:43,752
you were a secretary to the late
Assemblyman Kim Myeong-jae.

291
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:45,254
I understand the confusion.

292
00:16:45,337 --> 00:16:46,547
-That'sâ€¦
-Goodbye.

293
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:56,974
How young and brash he is.

294
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:00,102
DAEHAN PARTY CHAIRWOMAN
WOO JIN-SEOK

295
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:03,022
I'm sure you're busy preparing
for the National Assembly inspection.

296
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:05,941
When did you prepare all this?

297
00:17:06,942 --> 00:17:09,069
I envy your youth.

298
00:17:10,779 --> 00:17:13,657
I've been hearing that a lot today.

299
00:17:15,617 --> 00:17:18,328
I was only elected four times so far,

300
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:21,540
but 15 and a half years
have passed in the blink of an eye.

301
00:17:22,791 --> 00:17:26,462
The Nation and People's Party is probably
to blame for some of these gray hairs.

302
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:28,839
I can count on you, right?

303
00:17:29,631 --> 00:17:31,842
We have eight months
until the general election.

304
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:34,428
The timing is just right.

305
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:36,722
I'll do my best.

306
00:17:36,805 --> 00:17:38,891
Sure. I don't worry one bit.

307
00:17:39,892 --> 00:17:43,020
You're the best our party has to offer.

308
00:17:58,494 --> 00:18:00,370
Do you like the view here?

309
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,664
The eighth floor isn't that low.

310
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:07,336
Haven't you been using
your office on the tenth floor

311
00:18:07,419 --> 00:18:09,379
since your first election?

312
00:18:09,463 --> 00:18:11,173
Yes, that's correct.

313
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:13,383
Why didn't you come down during this term?

314
00:18:14,802 --> 00:18:16,637
Did you feel like you didn't deserve it

315
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:20,265
because you were
only a list member last time?

316
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:21,767
Not at all.

317
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:26,522
I signed up for the same room
because I wanted to remain humble.

318
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:29,817
Humble?

319
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:34,029
Eight years of humility
is more than enough.

320
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:37,533
Once this general election pans out,

321
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:39,284
you'd be elected for the third time.

322
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:42,079
You'll be able to pick
any office you like.

323
00:18:45,457 --> 00:18:47,167
Would you like this room instead?

324
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:50,254
I'm a bit tired of that view now.

325
00:18:50,838 --> 00:18:52,172
No, I'm fine.

326
00:18:52,256 --> 00:18:56,176
Or sign up for the room
on the sixth floor that the president used

327
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:58,428
during his time as an assemblyman.

328
00:18:58,512 --> 00:19:02,391
The competition for that room
is quite fierce.

329
00:19:03,225 --> 00:19:06,562
But if you want it,
I can pull some strings.

330
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:09,731
I couldn't possibly do that
during my third term.

331
00:19:10,357 --> 00:19:12,109
I'm content with my current room.

332
00:19:13,193 --> 00:19:15,362
You sure aren't greedy.

333
00:19:19,199 --> 00:19:21,952
I can't say that I'm not greedy at all.

334
00:19:23,036 --> 00:19:24,746
Why else would I be here?

335
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:30,002
You see,

336
00:19:30,794 --> 00:19:32,838
none of the offices
anywhere in this building

337
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:35,299
have a view of Bugaksan
like the Blue House does.

338
00:19:44,766 --> 00:19:45,767
That's right.

339
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:49,104
As long as you're in Yeouido, that is.

340
00:19:52,232 --> 00:19:54,067
Pardon my thoughtlessness.

341
00:19:55,485 --> 00:19:58,238
Your current office
will soon become the office

342
00:19:58,822 --> 00:20:01,491
that the assemblymen will compete to have.

343
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:09,499
-Hello.
-Hello.

344
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:10,667
What's next?

345
00:20:11,168 --> 00:20:13,712
You have an interview with SBC.

346
00:20:13,795 --> 00:20:16,173
Honey, I'll be home
around midnight tonight.

347
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:18,842
Guess what?
I got called young twice today.

348
00:20:18,926 --> 00:20:21,386
-And for dinnerâ€¦
-How do you like having a young husband?

349
00:20:22,179 --> 00:20:23,138
Okay.

350
00:20:25,432 --> 00:20:28,352
DEOKSUNG MILL

351
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:48,413
HOW DO YOU LIKE HAVING A YOUNG HUSBAND?

352
00:20:49,122 --> 00:20:50,207
Jeez.

353
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:54,795
Good for you.

354
00:20:54,878 --> 00:20:56,964
But I'll always be younger than you.

355
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:02,552
Come on. We're almost the same age.

356
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:05,847
-Are you here for oil?
-Yes.

357
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:09,059
No one's in, right?

358
00:21:09,142 --> 00:21:10,435
She must be out.

359
00:21:11,186 --> 00:21:13,272
Her granddaughter passed away.

360
00:21:14,564 --> 00:21:15,565
I'm sorry?

361
00:21:17,317 --> 00:21:20,279
She was a university student.
She hanged herself.

362
00:21:20,362 --> 00:21:21,697
NAMGOONG SOL

363
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:23,156
She fought with her boyfriend,

364
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:26,576
and he threatened to spread
some embarrassing photos of her.

365
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:30,330
But the police haven't even
arrested that bastard.

366
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:33,959
He's apparently a medical student.

367
00:21:34,042 --> 00:21:37,754
They didn't arrest him
saying that he wouldn't flee.

368
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:42,467
Excuse me. Do I know you?

369
00:21:44,886 --> 00:21:46,722
Right. You came by the mill yesterday.

370
00:21:52,436 --> 00:21:53,687
Please eat.

371
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:58,900
How did you come all the way here?

372
00:22:02,279 --> 00:22:04,531
She lost her parents at a young age,

373
00:22:05,741 --> 00:22:08,577
so I raised her with the utmost care

374
00:22:09,661 --> 00:22:11,079
to the best of my abilities.

375
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:16,835
But the police won't even
arrest that bastard.

376
00:22:36,605 --> 00:22:37,856
ROOM 5
NAMGOONG SOL

377
00:22:37,939 --> 00:22:38,940
Look.

378
00:22:39,649 --> 00:22:42,611
Please sign the guest book
before you leave.

379
00:22:43,445 --> 00:22:45,864
I'm so grateful that you came,

380
00:22:45,947 --> 00:22:47,657
so I want to remember you.

381
00:22:48,575 --> 00:22:50,619
Will you do that for me?

382
00:22:51,828 --> 00:22:54,122
-It's fine.
-But stillâ€¦

383
00:22:54,706 --> 00:22:55,707
Right.

384
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:58,001
I have your perilla oil ready.

385
00:22:58,627 --> 00:23:01,046
Don't worry about it. I'll come by later.

386
00:23:01,671 --> 00:23:03,256
All right, then.

387
00:23:06,968 --> 00:23:08,220
Sol used to tell me

388
00:23:09,221 --> 00:23:12,682
to close down the mill and stop working.

389
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:17,312
She said I didn't have to work
because she had a part-time job.

390
00:23:19,314 --> 00:23:21,566
But now I'm glad
that I didn't listen to her

391
00:23:22,359 --> 00:23:24,319
to be able to have a guest at her funeral.

392
00:23:26,363 --> 00:23:29,282
Thank you so much for coming.

393
00:23:29,825 --> 00:23:31,034
I mean it.

394
00:23:32,119 --> 00:23:34,830
Don't mention it. I'll be going now.

395
00:23:44,214 --> 00:23:45,048
Go on.

396
00:24:01,273 --> 00:24:02,941
CLEAN, HONEST, AND COMPETENT WORKER
NAM JOONG-DO

397
00:24:03,024 --> 00:24:05,193
A special education school
next to a regular one?

398
00:24:05,277 --> 00:24:07,112
That's just absurd.

399
00:24:07,195 --> 00:24:09,739
It's important that we build this school
for disabled children

400
00:24:09,823 --> 00:24:11,992
who struggle to travel long distances.

401
00:24:12,075 --> 00:24:15,162
We only have a bus from Manil-dong
to Jicheong Station every 20 minutes,

402
00:24:15,245 --> 00:24:17,581
which is just too long.

403
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:21,251
All the other buses come by
every 6 to 13 minutes at most.

404
00:24:21,751 --> 00:24:22,919
-That's quite a difference.
-It is.

405
00:24:23,003 --> 00:24:24,254
-Well noted.
-Please check.

406
00:24:24,838 --> 00:24:27,883
We can't have such large vehicles
driving by where children commute.

407
00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:31,928
Despite being a school zone,
there's too much speeding.

408
00:24:32,012 --> 00:24:34,848
She's right. It's a very dangerous area.

409
00:24:34,931 --> 00:24:36,766
Right. I agree.

410
00:24:39,352 --> 00:24:42,189
Please give me a call
through the number on my card

411
00:24:42,272 --> 00:24:43,940
if you need anything else.

412
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:47,319
Is this your personal number?
Not your secretary's?

413
00:24:47,402 --> 00:24:48,987
Yes, it's mine.

414
00:24:49,070 --> 00:24:51,448
I'll be picking up, so call me anytime.

415
00:24:51,531 --> 00:24:53,241
I see. Thank you.

416
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:55,410
-Goodbye.
-This way.

417
00:24:55,493 --> 00:24:57,162
-Thank you.
-Goodbye.

418
00:24:57,245 --> 00:24:58,788
Thank you for your time, everyone.

419
00:25:00,457 --> 00:25:02,542
-Thank you.
-Thank you. Goodbye.

420
00:25:03,084 --> 00:25:03,919
Good work.

421
00:25:04,419 --> 00:25:05,962
Gosh, what a busy day.

422
00:25:09,674 --> 00:25:13,720
Do you really answer
all their calls yourself?

423
00:25:13,803 --> 00:25:15,180
Of course.

424
00:25:15,805 --> 00:25:17,849
I may not be able to resolve everything,

425
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:21,269
but it provides a chance
to vent their frustrations and feel heard.

426
00:25:21,853 --> 00:25:24,773
Speaking directly with an assemblyman
provides some assurance.

427
00:25:26,066 --> 00:25:28,777
Some of them curse me out
as soon as I pick up,

428
00:25:29,444 --> 00:25:31,279
but I'll live longer thanks to them.

429
00:25:32,864 --> 00:25:36,493
I'll give you a summary
of today's discussions later.

430
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:37,452
Okay. Thank you.

431
00:25:38,286 --> 00:25:40,205
We finished much earlier than I thought.

432
00:25:41,206 --> 00:25:42,999
When's the dinner with our sponsor?

433
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:45,377
At 7 p.m. at Haniljeong.

434
00:26:03,895 --> 00:26:05,897
SINYANG-GU WOMEN AND YOUTH SHELTER

435
00:26:13,571 --> 00:26:14,781
THANK YOU FOR THE DELIVERY
ENJOY

436
00:26:48,648 --> 00:26:49,941
Is that you, Yoon-seo?

437
00:26:52,610 --> 00:26:54,779
-Mom!
-What is it this time?

438
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:57,574
Did you say I can't go to SNU this Sunday?

439
00:26:57,657 --> 00:26:59,909
-Yes.
-Why?

440
00:26:59,993 --> 00:27:03,330
My friends' parents are
pulling all the strings they can

441
00:27:03,413 --> 00:27:04,998
to beef up their kids' resumes.

442
00:27:05,582 --> 00:27:08,418
It's not like I asked Dad for help.

443
00:27:08,501 --> 00:27:10,920
So why would you decline their help?

444
00:27:12,047 --> 00:27:14,716
How can a middle school student
be credited as a co-author?

445
00:27:14,799 --> 00:27:17,385
What can you even do to help
a professor with his thesis?

446
00:27:17,469 --> 00:27:19,846
There must be something.
He told us to come.

447
00:27:19,929 --> 00:27:21,473
You don't even know anything.

448
00:27:21,556 --> 00:27:23,016
Of course I do.

449
00:27:23,099 --> 00:27:24,726
You didn't even go to university.

450
00:27:29,147 --> 00:27:29,981
Sorry.

451
00:27:31,274 --> 00:27:32,692
That may be true,

452
00:27:32,776 --> 00:27:35,779
but I know that it's absurd
for you to be credited as a co-author.

453
00:27:35,862 --> 00:27:37,614
Dad would have said no too if he--

454
00:27:37,697 --> 00:27:39,866
There you go, bringing him up again.

455
00:27:39,949 --> 00:27:41,785
Stop using him as your excuse.

456
00:27:41,868 --> 00:27:45,288
Why can't I do what all my friends do
just because of him?

457
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:48,249
Jeez. This is so annoying.

458
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:51,044
Yoon-seo, we're not done talking.

459
00:27:51,127 --> 00:27:54,005
Forget it. I won't go, all right?

460
00:27:54,089 --> 00:27:56,716
Yoon-seo, stop right there.

461
00:27:58,718 --> 00:27:59,677
Yoon-seo.

462
00:28:01,221 --> 00:28:03,598
Did you lock the door? Open up.

463
00:28:03,681 --> 00:28:05,266
Go away. I'm going to study.

464
00:28:05,350 --> 00:28:09,437
Really? You're going to be
in serious trouble, young lady.

465
00:28:09,521 --> 00:28:10,814
Nam Yoon-seo.

466
00:28:24,285 --> 00:28:25,703
I'm sorry.

467
00:28:25,787 --> 00:28:28,415
He texted me saying he was almost home.

468
00:28:30,166 --> 00:28:32,961
Why the long face? Is it Yoon-seo?

469
00:28:34,963 --> 00:28:38,466
She's acting out more and more.

470
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:40,718
She's going through puberty.
Ji-hoon was the same.

471
00:28:41,678 --> 00:28:44,305
I feel terrible the moment
I'm done scolding them.

472
00:28:45,515 --> 00:28:47,684
Maybe it's because he's a politician,

473
00:28:47,767 --> 00:28:50,687
but I don't think we're doing
as well as other parents are.

474
00:28:51,438 --> 00:28:53,523
You two are doing a terrific job.

475
00:28:54,899 --> 00:28:57,610
Right. Do you want to use Ji-hoon's room?

476
00:28:57,694 --> 00:28:59,946
Me? Why? I already have a room.

477
00:29:00,530 --> 00:29:01,781
Your room is too small

478
00:29:01,865 --> 00:29:04,868
because it was
my late mother-in-law's storage room.

479
00:29:05,368 --> 00:29:07,370
Had we known you'd be living with us,

480
00:29:07,454 --> 00:29:10,540
we would have built a room for you
upstairs when we first moved in.

481
00:29:10,623 --> 00:29:13,084
Forget it.
The upstairs is for your family.

482
00:29:13,168 --> 00:29:14,377
I'm fine with my room.

483
00:29:16,713 --> 00:29:20,258
Yeo-jin, you know
how grateful I am for you, right?

484
00:29:21,384 --> 00:29:25,180
When my mother-in-law passed away
and I was pregnant with Yoon-seo,

485
00:29:25,263 --> 00:29:26,890
I was going through so much.

486
00:29:27,557 --> 00:29:29,350
Had you not offered to live together,

487
00:29:29,434 --> 00:29:31,728
I wouldn't have been
able to endure it all.

488
00:29:32,687 --> 00:29:34,189
Thank you so much.

489
00:29:40,528 --> 00:29:42,238
-I'm home.
-Hey.

490
00:29:43,448 --> 00:29:45,658
You're home awfully early today.

491
00:29:45,742 --> 00:29:47,202
I should take a breather too.

492
00:29:48,077 --> 00:29:49,621
You're still up? It's late.

493
00:29:50,205 --> 00:29:51,414
She wanted to have a beer.

494
00:29:51,498 --> 00:29:52,916
Why? Did I do something wrong?

495
00:29:52,999 --> 00:29:54,250
Why? Are you feeling guilty?

496
00:29:55,835 --> 00:29:57,420
Recycling is tomorrow.

497
00:29:57,504 --> 00:29:59,297
I haven't done anything wrong.

498
00:30:00,715 --> 00:30:02,592
-Give it to me.
-Thank you. I enjoyed it.

499
00:30:02,675 --> 00:30:03,843
No problem.

500
00:30:03,927 --> 00:30:06,054
Give it to me. I'll wash it with the rest.

501
00:30:06,137 --> 00:30:07,305
No, I can do it.

502
00:30:07,388 --> 00:30:08,681
Just give it to me.

503
00:30:09,182 --> 00:30:11,226
How can you make him vegetable juice

504
00:30:11,309 --> 00:30:13,269
every morning for the past eight years?

505
00:30:13,353 --> 00:30:16,147
But this is the only thing
that I'm doing for him.

506
00:30:16,231 --> 00:30:18,775
Exactly. I didn't bargain well.

507
00:30:18,858 --> 00:30:21,277
I should have asked
for some other things too.

508
00:30:21,361 --> 00:30:22,946
-Rest up. Thanks.
-Okay.

509
00:30:23,029 --> 00:30:24,614
-Good night.
-You too.

510
00:30:25,782 --> 00:30:27,408
-Good night.
-Good night.

511
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:40,380
You must be exhausted.
Wash up and go to bed, honey.

512
00:30:47,804 --> 00:30:49,222
Why are you staring at me?

513
00:30:49,973 --> 00:30:51,349
My face is flushed, isn't it?

514
00:30:54,727 --> 00:30:55,812
